'''Steve Binder''' (born [[December 12]], [[1930s#1932|1932]]) is the credited director of ''[[The Star Wars Holiday Special]]''. He replaced [[David Acomba]], who left during the middle of the production because of "artistic differences." One scene directed by Binder was the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|cantina]] sequence with [[Bea Arthur]] and [[Harvey Korman]].<ref name="Starlog">{{Starlog|19|Starlog (magazine)|'Star Wars' Invades TV}}</ref>

An Emmy Award-winner,<ref>{{WebCite|url=https://www.emmys.com/bios/steve-binder|text=Steve Binder|work=[https://www.emmys.com emmys.com]|archivedate=20210304074133}}</ref> Binder has been working in television since the 1960s. He has directed TV specials featuring musicians such as [[Wikipedia:Liza Minnelli|Liza Minnelli]], [[Wikipedia:Elvis Presley|Elvis Presley]], [[Wikipedia:Mac Davis|Mac Davis]], [[Wikipedia:Barry Manilow|Barry Manilow]], [[Wikipedia:Olivia Newton-John|Olivia Newton-John]], and [[Wikipedia:Diana Ross|Diana Ross]].

